# .dockerignore — kept in sync with .gitignore (match dockerignore to gitignore).
#
# IMPORTANT semantic difference: unlike .gitignore, a bare `*.egg-info/` or
# `__pycache__/` here matches ONLY the context root, NOT every depth. Git treats
# the same patterns as "match at any depth". That mismatch is why src/eedom/
# (stale __pycache__ bytecode) and src/eedom.egg-info/ were being copied into the
# test image and tripping tests/unit/test_source_tree_guard.py. The fix: prefix
# depth-anywhere patterns with `**/` so they mirror .gitignore.
#
# Patterns that are root-anchored in .gitignore (they contain a `/`) stay
# root-anchored here. `package.json`/`package-lock.json` are scoped to the root on
# purpose: the e2e fixtures under tests/e2e/fixtures/ carry force-tracked
# package.json inputs that the scanners must see, so they must NOT be excluded.

# VCS + container scratch (never part of a build)
.git/
cdk.out/

# Python
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*$py.class
**/*.egg-info/
**/*.egg
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.venv/

# Testing & coverage
**/.pytest_cache/
**/htmlcov/
**/.coverage
**/.mypy_cache/

# Linting & formatting
**/.ruff_cache/

# Environment & secrets
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# macOS
**/.DS_Store
**/.AppleDouble
**/.LSOverride

# WFC pipeline state
**/.runs/
**/.temp/
**/.wfc/

# Serena tooling
**/.serena/

# Browser-gate screenshot artifacts (scripts/screenshots.ts output)
**/screenshots/

# Node (used only for tooling, not runtime) — root only (fixtures keep theirs)
**/node_modules/
package.json
package-lock.json

# Runtime artifacts (generated, not committed)
**/evidence/
**/diagrams/
**/*.svg
!assets/*.svg
**/*.zip
.caliper/reports/
.caliper/code_graph.sqlite
.claude/worktrees/
**/.worktrees/

# Local infrastructure (never commit)
.dogfood/
.dogood/
docs/pitch-page/
**/.scratch/

# Sandbox container-test scratch (CA-injected build workaround — env-specific)
Dockerfile.ci-test
Dockerfile.test.ci
**/cabuild/
egress-gateway-ca-*.crt
swp-ca-*.crt
